main event: A Ground-Radar operator observed one unidentified object on the radar screen at Johnson Island on 17 September 1961.
interesting points: The object was tracked at a distance of approximately 20 miles,The object was observed for approximately 40 seconds before disappearing,The estimated speed of the object was between 1200-1500 knots,There were comments indicating insufficient data for further evaluation of the sighting,Other crew members reported observing a U.F.O. nearby with similarities to the radar observation.
